Bidvest Wits lost 1-0 to Egyptian giants Al Ahly in their Caf Champions League first round, first leg tie in Cairo on Saturday night.The Clever Boys spent most of the match defending, capitulating to a Ahmad Hegazi's 57th-minute strike.The second leg will be played at Bidvest Stadium on Sunday.In the Caf Confederation Cup Platinum Stars lost 1-0 away against Vipers FC in Kampala, Uganda in their first leg match.- TMG Digital/TMG Sport